            <abstract id="ref24" label="Abstract">In 1979 the staff of the New-York Historical Society began an organizing drive with District 65, United Automobile Workers of America. Victory in the union elections led to contract negotiations, and the staff conducted a six month strike before signing a collective bargaining agreement in 1980. This collection contains newspaper clippings, photographs, minutes from the negotiating committee, copies of contracts, and leaflets.</abstract>
            <langmaterial id="ref25" label="Language of Materials note">Materials are in English</langmaterial>
