        </accessrestrict>
        <bioghist id="ref6">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>In 1979 the staff of the New-York Historical Society began an organizing drive with District 65, United Automobile Workers of America. Victory in the union elections led to contract negotiations later in the same year. The negotiations were unsuccessful, and the staff conducted a six month strike before signing a collective bargaining agreement in 1980.</p>
            <p>John Lovari was a reference librarian at the New-York Historical Society, head of the negotiating committee, and after an agreement was reached, a shop steward.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <userestrict id="ref7">
            <head>Use Restrictions</head>
            <p>Coyright (and related rights to publicity and privacy) to materials in this collection created by John Lovari are held by John Lovari. Permission to publish or reproduce materials to which he holds copyright must be secured from the copyright holder. Please contact the Tamiment Library for assistance with contacting John Lovari.</p>
        </userestrict>
        <processinfo id="ref9">
            <head>Processing Information note</head>
            <p>No original order was apparent on receipt of the materials from the donor. The materials were grouped by topic and placed in archival folders and boxes.</p>
        </processinfo>
        <arrangement id="ref10">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>Materials are arranged in alphabetical order by topic.</p>
        </arrangement>
